==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ge
<hw>Ge</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>The chemical symbol for germanium, a
metalloid element of atomic number 32. See <er>germanium</er>.</def>
<wns>[wns=1]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> germanium.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ge</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Ge
<hw>Ge</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Mythol.)</fld> <def>goddess of the earth
and mother of Cronus and the Titans in ancient mythology. See
<er>Gaea</er>.</def> <wns>[wns=2]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Gaea, Gaia.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ge-</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Ge-
<hw>Ge-</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>An Anglo-Saxon prefix. See
<er>Y-</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Geal</ent>⟦br⟧
